# Chapter 10: Managing Data Frames with the `dplyr` Package
## `dplyr` Grammar
The `dplyr` package provides an optimized set of routines based on a
grammar. Some of the verbs in this grammar are
* `select`: returna  subset of the columns of a dataframe
* `filter`: extract a subset of rows from a data frame based on
  logical conditions
* `arrange`: reorder rows of a data frame
* `rename`: rename variables in a data frame
* `mutate`: add new variables/columns or transform 
